1. HTML Structure
   Use semantic elements:

<header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, and <footer>.

Create a clear heading hierarchy using <h1> to <h6>.

## Use emphasis tags like <strong> and <em> where appropriate.

2. CSS Styling
   Apply CSS Box Model concepts:

Use margin, padding, and border for spacing and sizing.

Use relative units (rem or em) for font sizes and spacing.

Create a card-style layout for at least one section:

## Add a box-shadow, padding, and rounded corners.

3. Flexbox Layout
   Build a responsive navigation menu using Flexbox:

Ensure it adapts to different screen sizes.

Implement a multi-column layout for your main content using Flexbox.

## Use Flexbox to center content both vertically and horizontally in at least one section.

4. Form Design
   Create a form with the following input types:

Text (<input type="text">)

Email (<input type="email">)

Password (<input type="password">)

Checkbox (<input type="checkbox">)

Radio buttons (<input type="radio">)

Style form elements with hover and focus states:

Change background color, border, or add transitions.

Implement basic form validation using HTML5 attributes:

Use required, minlength, pattern, etc.
